node.text:
Can you believe it’s been that long? I do wish these two best friends more years together and more adventures.
Hope you enjoy this video of special little moments throughout the 6 years of the best friendship ever.

Tag your best friend! 💛
#BeTheWatsonToMyKiko 

A special thank you to @bronzeradio for allowing us to use this song for this very special video.

Song: Right There Beside You
By: @bronzeradio

____

This past summer we took Kiko camping to Glacier many times. We live not to far from that place so I thought it would be a good idea to take my sweet boy camping and swimming as a way to help him heal and forget all he went through.
I have to say it helped all those awesome adventures he have been going to. It keeps him happy, energetic and not sad or depressed. Adventures and nature is a great way to help him keep positive through his cancer fight.

In the first part of the video you can also see scenes of our @rei photo. The boys and I are so proud of that capture.

node.text:
Sharing Watson and Kiko’s story to our Spanish community for the first time 💛
__________
Watson y Kiko. Hermanos y mejores amigos. Kiko llegó a nuestra vida cuando tenia 4 años. Watson tenía 7 meses pero el momento en el que se conocieron por primera vez su conexión fue fuerte. Llevan cuatro años de amistad y compartiendo aventuras.

Este verano pasado Kiko fue diagnosticado con cancer en los huesos. Un cancer bastante agresivo fue lo que nos dijeron. Para evitar que el cancer pasara a otros lados su patita tuvo que ser amputada. Gracias a que lo detectamos a tiempo y tomamos acción Kiko tiene la oportunidad de vivir más tiempo del que los veterinarios asumieron. Pero nada es seguro todo podría cambiar en un instante.

Ya an pasado 6 meses. Kiko se ve con mucha energía y continua disfrutando de la vida a lado de su mejor amigo y hermano Watson. Que lo abraza cada vez que puede y le brinda apoyo.
No sabemos cómo se ve el futuro es por eso que vivimos cada instante con Kiko como si fuera el último. Por que no es solo un perro para nosotros, el es nuestra familia y lo amamos como tal.
Doy gracias por tener dos adorables canes que me brindan tanta alegría a diario. Al final se qué Kiko terminara por rompernos el corazón a todos pero los bellos momentos que nos a dado y continua dando vale la pena pasar por el dolor, no lo cambiaria por nada.

It’s been four moths since Kiko got diagnosed. He was given 4-6 months.  But calculating since we noticed the pain in his leg that we thought it was arthritis its actually been more than that.
The battle is not over but he continues this journey strong.  He is surrounded by love, compassion and so much support. Not only from his family but by all of you who follow his story, THANK YOU.

He lost his leg but not his wild spirit.
-
All credit to song goes to Grizfolk, Spoonful.

Kiko loves napping on his back. When he recently got his leg amputated it was very challenging for him to keep his balance.
After some time when the pain went away and he was getting used to his new self he went back to napping the way he LOVES to. And I’m so glad I captured it on video because it was the cutest thing ever.
I also added some other sweet moments in there 💛

I came to realize that three legged dogs look extra cute sleeping.

❤️ Calendar Giveaway 

Before our calendars are up for sale we wanted to give one away.

This year’s calendar is dedicated to Watson and Kiko’s friendship. All photos in it are the ones I captured throughout the years of their friendship. It also includes Wats and Kiko’s birthday’s and actual paw prints in each page 😍

This is a very special calendar.
__________

How to enter:

🔸Follow @wat.ki 
🔸Tag a few friends below

This giveaway is open to everyone so international entries are welcome.

Contest end September 8th 2021 at midnight. The winner will be announced September 10th.

Calendars will be up for purchase September 13th on our Etsy shop. 
————

Thank you for all the love and support. We love you all and good luck.
